	     Durban - It was the missing baby story that brought the nation to a standstill. Then one-month-old baby Siwaphiwe was reported missing by her mother, S'bongile Mbambo, after an alleged hijacking which she claimed happened in Greyville, Durban in March. Read more: Baby Siwaphiwe's mother arrested for kidnapping After a massive two day search by police the baby was finally found in a car on the N3 highway near the Mariannhill toll plaza around midnight on 12 March, but further investigation revealed S'bongile Mbambo lied about the kidnapping and she and her lover then faced charges of fraud and defeating the ends of justice, as reported by News24. The accused appeared in the Durban Magistrate’s Court on Wednesday morning and S’bongile Mbambo has pleaded guilty to kidnapping and admitted that she made a false allegation when reporting that her baby was missing. She is due back in court on January 22, 2018 for sentencing. Read more: Who will care for baby Siwaphiwe?     24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  